# TypeScript Standards

## Typing

- Use `ProType` and `PropertyTag` discriminated unions from `types/safeFile.ts` — avoid `any` except transitional `StructProp.value`.
- Prefer `bigint` for `Int64Property` values.

## Binary reads

- All endianness and string decoding go through `BinaryReader` — no ad-hoc `DataView` in decoder layers.
- Use `DataView` and typed arrays; avoid manual bit shifts for primitives.
- Reuse `tracker/decoder/decoder.ts` `toHex` for debug hex output.

## Imports

- Path alias: `tracker/` (see `vite.config.ts` / `tsconfig`).
- Type-only imports: `import type { ... }`.

## Platform

- No polyfills for legacy engines.
- No Node-only APIs in `src/` — browser and Vitest only.

## Changes to parser code

Run `pnpm test` before finishing. Add focused Vitest cases with small `Uint8Array` fixtures for new read paths.
